<http://www.spektrix.com/capilanouniversity/event/8601AVPPNNBTVGDHCLBCTPRSLGQPDSBRD>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Jenn Grant";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Jenn Grant – \"Queen of the Strait: Cradled by the Waves\"</h1><span><br/></span>Acclaimed Canadian artist Jenn Grant invites audiences into an unforgettable new world with <span class=\"ItalicText\">Cradled by the Waves</span>, a ground-breaking live tour that transforms her forthcoming album, <span class=\"ItalicText\">Queen of the Strait</span>, into a stunning multimedia performance blending music, film, theatre, and dance. Grant’s most personal work to date, <span class=\"ItalicText\">Queen of the Strait</span> draws from her childhood in Prince Edward Island and the timeless pull of the Atlantic. The live experience reimagines those songs in motion-a moving meditation on grief, transformation, and the beauty of beginning again.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Each show is an immersive, cinematic experience, featuring a six-piece band, curated film sequences, and interpretive movement. Together, these elements create a dreamlike landscape where the songs flow seamlessly into one another.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Step through the portal and be part of a shared moment that blurs the line between audience and artist-a living, breathing work of art that changes with every performance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Halifax, Nova Scotia-based Jenn Grant is a three-time Juno-nominated singer-songwriter, whose music has been described as “the aural equivalent of a warm embrace” (Pop Matters) and “dreamy, harp-and-woodwinds folk, the work of a painter born in paradise” (The Age, AU). With eight albums to date, she has earned widespread recognition for her ethereal sound and evocative storytelling.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.capilanou.ca/student-services/community/blueshore-financial-centre-for-the-performing-arts/our-events/all-events/events/jenn-grant--queen-of-the-strait-cradled-by-the-waves.php\">Show Info</a>
""";
