<http://www.spektrix.com/capilanouniversity/event/8401ACDNQDNDVRQCTJQRQPHVTKLNTCVJH>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Novalima + Empanadas Ilegales";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Novalima takes place at The Rickshaw Theatre</h1><span><br/></span>From Lima, Peru, Novalima fuses traditional Afro-Peruvian rhythms with cutting-edge electronic, dub, reggae, salsa, and global beats. With six acclaimed albums, a Latin Grammy nomination and multiple performances at top festivals worldwide, Novalima has become a pioneer in modern Afro-Peruvian music. Their music bridges cultural and generational gaps, uniting audiences through infectious rhythms and a deep connection to their roots. Novalima consists of four core members: Ramon Perez Prieto, Grimaldo del Solar, Rafael Morales, and Carlos Li Carrillo, with additional percussionists joining for live shows.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Sharing the Rickshaw stage for this show is Vancouver's own psychedelic cumbia and salsa ensemble Empanadas Ilegales. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This show is presented by BlueShore at CapU, Rickshaw Theatre and Caravan World Rhythms.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">E-tickets not available for this production. Tickets will be mailed or available for pick up at The Rickshaw Theatre. </span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://rickshawtheatre.com/\">The Rickshaw Theatre Website</a><span><br/></span>
""";
